    "ACJ was also trialed by Ellison (2023)-avoiding rubrics but encouraging assessment by comparing different pieces of work.",
    "However, improvements in attainment were not measured.",
    "Four papers (5%) addressed a variety of topics.",
    "\"Free riding\" was defined by Chiu et al. (2020) as exploiting another's work or taking credit for work done by others without contributing to a team project.",
    "An online assessment system for individual scores (OASIS) was designed to reduce student perceptions of free riding, including: contractual commitment, team discussion, median peer assessment of each member's contribution, assessment revision opportunities, conditional teacher participation and final appeal."
